GameDay Live: Brady, Patriots answer to tie game Bruce Lerch Photo by: Associated Press New England Patriots quarterback Tom Brady (12) passes against the New York Jets during the first half of an NFL football game, Sunday, Oct. 25, 2015, in Foxborough, Mass. (AP Photo/Steven Senne) Photo by: Associated Press New York Jets quarterback Ryan Fitzpatrick (14) passes against New England Patriots defensive end Rob Ninkovich (50) during the first half of an NFL football game, Sunday, Oct. 25, 2015, in Foxborough, Mass. (AP Photo/Charles Krupa) Photo by: Associated Press New York Jets quarterback Ryan Fitzpatrick (14) fumbles as New England Patriots defensive end Chandler Jones (95) gives chase during the first half of an NFL football game, Sunday, Oct. 25, 2015, in Foxborough, Mass. (AP Photo/Charles Krupa) Photo by: Matt Stone Tom Brady warms up before the game today against the New York Jets at Gillette Stadium. Photo by: Matt Stone Patriots special teamer Matthew Slater warms up before the game today at Gillette Stadium. Though he struggled with an injury all week, Slater was active for the matchup against the Jets. Photo by: Herald graphic Game Day Live prev next comments Tweet Live Blog Game Day Live: Jets vs Patriots It's Jets week.
There's a new boss in New York/ New Jersey, but will today's tilt be the same old Patriots-Jets, or will Todd Bowles' team have something extra as they try and wrest control of the AFC East from New England? Join Bruce Lerch and the Herald staff for a live chat of today's 1 p.m. game in Foxboro as the Pats look to run their record to 6-0.
